<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="69" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1404,2007]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,379,1548,1574]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer roundly rectangular posteriad, bearing numerous setae scattered on surface, with or without dorsal process. Subgenital plate moderately long, about twice as long as valve, with concave outer margin, bearing macrosetae arranged in oblique row across plate and numerous fine setae on dorsal margin and apex. Style broad, with short apophysis and large preapical lobe. Connective T-shaped, with or without central lobe. Aedeagus tubular and slender, without process; shaft semicircular, curved dorsally; gonopore apical.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,848,1728,1755]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1404,2007]" box="[199,848,1728,1755]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1728,1754]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Distribution.</emphasis>
Palearctic region, Oriental region (
<collectingRegion box="[747,844,1728,1755]" country="China" name="Taiwan)" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Taiwan)</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="69" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1404,2007]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1764,1790]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Remarks.</emphasis>
This genus was synonymized under 
<taxonomicName authority="Matsumura" authorityName="Matsumura" authorityYear="1932" box="[746,979,1765,1791]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Igutettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[746,839,1765,1790]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Igutettix</emphasis>
Matsumura
</taxonomicName>
, because of the misidentification of the 
<typeStatus box="[151,199,1801,1827]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">type</typeStatus>
species of that genus by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dworakowska, I." box="[481,741,1800,1827]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" pagination="97 - 139" refId="ref6637" refString="Dworakowska, I. (1993 b) Fusiplata Ahmed and some other Dikraneurini (Insects, Auchenorrhyncha, Cicadellidae: Typhlocybinae). Entomologische Abhandlungen Staatliches Museum fur Tierkunde Dresden, 55 (7), 97 - 139." type="journal article" year="1993">Dworakowska (1993b)</bibRefCitation>
. However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Anufriev" authorityYear="1970" box="[868,1000,1800,1826]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Vilbasteana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[868,1000,1800,1826]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Vilbasteana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be distinguished by the following features: fore wing 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[383,399,1836,1850]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">nd</superScript>
apical cell stalked or pointed basally, hind wing vein CuA branched more basally, subgenital plates of male genitalia not fused to valve, style broad, and aedeagus simple. These features are common to 
<taxonomicName authority="Chiang, Hsu et Knight" authorityName="Chiang, Hsu et Knight" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraafrakra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Paraafrakra</emphasis>
Chiang, Hsu et Knight
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[538,623,1908,1934]" name="Taiwan" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, and accordingly, 
<taxonomicName box="[824,964,1908,1934]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraafrakra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[824,964,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Paraafrakra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is newly synonymized under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Anufriev" authorityYear="1970" box="[1298,1430,1908,1934]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Vilbasteana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1298,1430,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Vilbasteana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As a result, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Anufriev" authorityYear="1970" box="[285,417,1944,1970]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Vilbasteana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[285,417,1944,1970]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Vilbasteana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
now comprises two species: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lindberg, 1929)" baseAuthorityName="Lindberg" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[744,1053,1944,1970]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Dicraneura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oculata">
<emphasis box="[744,855,1944,1970]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">V. oculata</emphasis>
(Lindberg, 1929)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1060,1183,1944,1970]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">comb. rev.</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Chiang, Hsu et Knight, 1990)" authorityName="Ohara &amp; Hayashi" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Chiang, Hsu et Knight" baseAuthorityYear="1990" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraafrakra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulva" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1197,1280,1944,1970]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">V. fulva</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Chiang, C. C. &amp; Hsu, T. C. &amp; Knight, W. J." pageId="6" pageNumber="69" pagination="23 - 34" refId="ref6484" refString="Chiang, C. C., Hsu, T. C. &amp; Knight, W. J. (1990) Studies on Taiwanese Typhlocybinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae) (III) tribe Dikraneurini. Journal of Taiwan Museum, 43 (1), 23 - 34." type="journal article" year="1990">Chiang, Hsu et Knight, 1990</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[342,471,1980,2006]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[342,471,1980,2006]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
